-- Italian Government Calls for Confidence Vote on Omnibus Decree
-- B y   C h i a r a   V a s a r r i
-- 2012-01-25T19:05:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-25/italian-government-calls-for-confidence-vote-on-omnibus-decree.html
Italy’s government asked for a
confidence vote on an “omnibus” decree at the Chamber of
Deputies, Parliamentary Affairs Minister Piero Giarda told
lawmakers in  Rome  today.  The confidence vote will be held tomorrow about 1 p.m.
while a second and final vote on the measures will be on Jan.
31, according to the chamber’s press office. The decree contains
multiple extentions on different issues.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chiara Vasarri in Rome at 
 cvasarri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jerrold Colten at 
 jcolten@bloomberg.net  